==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tift
<hw>Tift</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Norw.
<ets>teft</ets> a scent. See <er>Tiff</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A
fit of pettishness, or slight anger; a tiff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>After all your fatigue you seem as ready for a <qex>tift</qex>
with me as if you had newly come from church.</q> <rj><qau>Blackwood's
Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tig</ent>⟦br⟧
